
[1]hypocritical

   HYPOCRIT'ICAL, a. Simulating; counterfeiting a religions character;
   assuming a false and deceitful appearance; applied to persons.

   1. Dissembling; concealing one's real character or motives.

   2. Proceeding from hypocrisy, or marking hypocrisy; as a hypocritical
   face or look.
